Vendored copies of 28 cosmology datasets (17 known-GT + 11 GT-free) from CP3-Origins/Things-to-bench
(gzipped CSVs; upstream commit 69a45dd, fetched 2026-07-10), the dataset companion of cp3-bench:
"cp3-bench: A tool for benchmarking symbolic regression algorithms tested with cosmology",
M. E. Thing & S. M. Koksbang, arXiv:2406.15531.

License: MIT (LICENSE.things-to-bench alongside; Copyright (c) 2023 CP3-Origins). The cp3-bench
tool repo (method wrappers, no data) is separately MIT.

Selection: 28 datasets in two tiers — the 17 known-GT sets (C1a-C1d LCDM H(z), C2a-C2b redshift
drift, C3g-C3h two-region backreaction closed forms, C5a-C5f NFW/Burkert profiles, C6a-C6c
GW-inspired h_plus toys; build input for `cp3-cosmo`, tools/build_cp3_cosmo.py) and the 11
GT-free discovery sets (C3a-C3f, C4a-C4e; build input for `cp3-blackbox`,
tools/build_cp3_blackbox.py — vendored later in P6, superseding this NOTICE's earlier
"not vendored" statement). The F1-F8 GP-toy re-renderings remain NOT vendored (dedup to our
DSO-derived suites); the F-set dedup and three upstream paper-vs-data discrepancies (C3h
sign/prefactor, C6a phase, C6c m2=m1) are documented in the catalog build reports.
